channel.title: [562] Tom's Cache Suite Help
channel.description: Okay, so I know Tom's Cache Suite is a little outdated for a 562 server and cache, but with a little work, it's not impossible to update it. Here's my question, though: does Jagex still use their old implementation of BZip2 for their cache? I know Tom's uses BZip2 to decrypt the Jagex cache archives, but I'm not sure if 562 cache still uses the same architecture. Can anyone help?
